Citations
Date: 11/8/1888
Source: Egmont Star
Author:
Vol / Page: 09
Edition:
Quote: The Committee recommend that New Zealand can be divided up into six sheep districts, with an Inspector over each. The six districts should be as follows: (1.) Otago and Southland (2.) Canterbury, Amuri and Kaikoura. (3.) Marlborough, Nelson and Westland. (4.) Wellington and Taranaki (5.) Hawkes Bay and Cook Country (6.) Auckland.
